				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\overline{1}$$\end{document} 0) facet on the ZnO catalyst is more favorable than the (0001) facet, as demonstrated by the DFT calculations (Fig. 19g, h) [268]. Experimental results further indicated that ZnO nanoparticles with a high fraction of (10 1¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
